The clock at St Katharinen church in Hamburg. (Daniel Reinhardt, dpa via AP) Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Berlin - A 20kg minute hand has fallen off a clock on a Hamburg church tower, plunging 40m onto the sidewalk below. Hamburg's fire service said on Sunday that the hand fell off the city's St Katharinen church overnight from Friday to Saturday, news agency dpa reported. No one was hurt. Fire officials checked the remaining hour hand and determined that it was firmly in place. It wasn't immediately clear what caused the roughly 2m hand to crash off the clock in the city in northern Germany. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  